How many Jan van Haasteren puzzles are there?

How many puzzles has Jan van Haasteren drawn in all those years? How many puzzles did Jan van Haasteren make (2023: turned 87)? This is not so easy to determine, as there are two items of interest that make it more complicated to determine this number:
- Within the Jan van Haasteren studio there are 3 artists: Jan van Haasteren himself, Dick Heins en Robert Derks. No longer working but used to be at the Studio Jan van Haasteren: Marco Eisinga. These puzzles are all released under the name Jan van Haasteren. But NOT all drawn by Jan van Haasteren!
– Various boxes have been released containing multiple puzzles, the following are the: 2-in-1, the 3-in-1, the 4-in-1, the 6-in-1 combi boxes. These boxes contain puzzles that also came out as a puzzle in a loose box of 1000 pieces. Then the puzzle is drawn once by, for example, Jan van Haasteren, but the same puzzle comes in a box of 1 pieces as well as in a combination box of 1000-in-2. But it was only drawn once. There are also 1 puzzles in a 1-in-2 box, do you count this as 1 puzzle (then count the boxes), or do you count this as two puzzles? In the latter case you sometimes count puzzles twice – since you already count them with a puzzle of 2 pieces in 1 box.
– You can also count the number of unique drawings made by ONE artist of the Jan van Haasteren Studio. I also made an overview. This gives another number, where you should know that these are drawings made by a draftsman of the Jan van Haasteren Studio.

So: How many Jan van Haasteren puzzles are there? As of October 6, 2024

If you count the number of boxes 856 Jan van Haasteren puzzles.
If you count the number of different drawings 273 Jan van Haasteren puzzles

How many puzzles were drawn per artist within the Jan van Haasteren studio?

I also made a count of the number of puzzles that were drawn per artist. However: I have not deduplicated. Example:
in the puzzle 80962 – '3 x 1000 Ice Hockey | Car paint shop | Camping Chaos (Intertoys edition)' are 3 puzzles, all drawn by Jan van Haasteren himself. However, all 3 of these puzzles were also released in a separate box of 1000 pieces. In this case, you are actually counting the puzzles twice. In my calculation, you will then arrive at 6 puzzles by Jan van Haasteren. With the numbers below, you will then arrive at a higher number than if you count the number of boxes above. But let it indicate the ratio between the artists of the Jan van Haasteren studio. So the number of puzzles drawn per artist of the Jan van Haasteren studio (as of October 6, 2024):
– Puzzles made by Jan van Haasteren himself: 666
– Puzzles made by Dick Heins: 52
– Puzzles made by Rob Derks: 59
– Puzzles made by Marco Eisinga: 7
– Puzzles made by Mars Greken: 4
– Puzzles made by Wilma van den Bosch: 13

More information about the puzzle publishers (abbreviations used)

In the tables below you can see that sometimes the same puzzle is published by another puzzle manufacturer. For example the puzzle 'safariof 1000 pieces. This is published by:
– JUMBO, in a Scandinavian edition, number 81453TT
– Holdson Funny World (HFW), number 09291
– Berverly Enterprises (BE), number 61-336

Jan van Haasteren puzzles 10 pieces

These are whole old puzzles en rare puzzles, but are very small. These are 3 puzzle cards that were included with the Bolletje rusk at the time. They were available in sets of 3 very small puzzles. There were 2 different sets of 3 puzzles. The nice thing is that you see that these puzzles are published by: AA ter Beek BV. From the website of Bolletje.nl do I get: “Bolletje was founded in 1867. Then Albertus Antonius ter Beek (AA ter Beek!) bought a bakery and shop for his son on Grotestraat Zuid in Almelo. Son Gerardus Johannes is then 24 and just married. He cooks something good out of it: around 1900 Gerard ter Beek already had thirteen employees. He is also modern, because at that time he was already working with an electric rye dough machine.”

Jan van Haasteren Vertical puzzles (1000 pieces)

An overview of all Vertical puzzles by Jan van Haasteren of 1000 pieces.
